• A person can maintain approx. 150 active relationships at a single time.

#InternationalDayofFriendship #Oxford #OxfordUni #OxfordUniversity

NEW RESEARCH: Data show the impact of #COVID19 on pregnant women. ⬇️ 

• 1 in 10 pregnant women admitted to hospital with symptoms need intensive care.

• Over 99% of pregnant women admitted to hospital with symptomatic COVID-19 are unvaccinated.

Marian Knight, Professor of Maternal and Child Population Health at the Nuffield Department of Population Health and chief investigator of the study, said, ‘It is extremely good news that so few vaccinated pregnant women have been admitted to hospital with COVID-19. However, it is very concerning that admissions of pregnant women to hospital with COVID-19 are increasing and that pregnant women appear to be more severely affected by the Delta variant of the disease.

I cannot emphasise more strongly how important it is for pregnant women to get vaccinated in order to protect both them and their baby. Until they are vaccinated, pregnant women must continue to be extremely attentive to social distancing measures including mask wearing, 2m distancing and meeting outdoors where possible.'

Read more ➡️ ox.ac.uk/news
